3: If anyone can do this, it's you, Reylas.
5:
I've been watching your growth for
some time, and today's the day you
come into your own!
11:
Heed me, spirits of water. Flowing
and formless, you have taken shape.
22:
Didn't I tell you? I knew you could
pull it off, Reylas.
42:
So you want to give your brother a
present, but aren't sure what to give?
46:
...As embarrassing as it is to admit,
I've got no experience with things
such as this.
49:
The holidays back home were little
more than an excuse for a handful
of elites to have an audience with
me.
58:
I know. I'm not able to save him yet,
but I still wish to celebrate with him.
61:
The magic I used to free the victim
earlier won't be enough... I believe 
I'll need the other Oculus to save 
my brother.
64:
That said, we made progress today,
did we not?
66:
And that fills with joy. I must go and
give my brother a progress report.
70:
I see... In that case, allow me to
assist you.
73:
I'll bring back a list of items
permitted for prisoners along with
an application form. I'm sure you'll
have many options to consider.
77:
By the way, what sort of gift did you
have in mind?
82:
I'm not certain just yet.
Unfortunately... I don't even know
what sorts of things my brother liked.
84:
It really sucks how we can't just ask
him. If only he could communicate
like I can...
87:
Well, there's something special
about this process, isn't there?
90:
It's not uncommon for a person to
be happy about a loved one taking
time out to consider what sort of gift
they might enjoy.
94:
Heh, agreed! It's the thought that
counts, right?
96:
So you're saying "Get him anything,
it doesn't matter"?
99:
Spending time in consideration of
the other person is a reflection of
one's own sincerity, hm?
102:
...Indeed it is. If only I had spent more
time together with Altair back then...
104:
To think that I haven't the slightest
idea what his interests were... We
should have been closer.
108:
Then GET closer after you thaw him
out. Your brother's still alive, you
know.
111:
Just get what you think is best and
let that brat whine about your
choice once he's free.
120:
...I bought what I could, 
but I wonder... Will he...
125: My apologies, are you all right?
135:
...This isn't your true form, I see.
Explain yourself, Dark Mage.
139:
Oh my, what a bothersome situation
I've gotten myself into.
141:
But no. I'm glad I didn't have to go
looking for you.
144:
Allow me to examine the power of
your Oculus directly!
148:
O darkness, slumbering in the void...
Reveal yourself to medeepest of
inner truths!
157:
But your effort is wasted. No matter
what you throw at me, I will recover
what you've taken from me!
160:
What I've taken from you? You really
don't understand your brother at all,
do you...
166:
You don't understand what it's like to
gaze up at the light from the
darkness. But then again, how could
you?
167:
But those eyes of yours that knew
nothing but light caused the
downfall of your own brother!
170:
The strong cannot understand the
thinking of the weak. The weak
perish because of this ignorance.
177: I cannot say I disagree with you.
180:
However, it isn't your place to make
such an accusation.
184:
You pretend to understand them,
and they are dragged into the
darkness by your deception,
exploited, and cast aside.
188:
Scum like you has no right to speak
of these things!
193:
Oh, geez. I guess I won't be getting
anywhere with this noble hero.
196:
Still, I appreciate your cooperation
with our little Oculus experiment, so
you can have that as thanks.
198:
But if you really care for your
brother, kill him. For someone as
desperate for the light as he is, no
gift could be more fitting.
210:
The Dark Mage was right... I still don't
understand you.
213:
I'm merely imposing upon you my
desire to make amends. This time,
at least...
216:
...That's why next year, directly, I'll ask
you what you want from me.
218:
You can complain as much as you
want, and I'll accept it all with a
happy heart.
